company_info.name: Yowie Group Limited
company_info.description: Yowie Group Limited, a brand licensing company, develops and sells consumer products worldwide. The company owns intellectual property rights to supply Yowie branded chocolate confectionery products, as well as develops Yowie digital platform and Yowie branded licensed consumer products. Yowie Group Limited is headquartered in Perth, Australia.
company_info.short_description: Yowie Group Limited, a brand licensing company, develops and sells consumer products worldwide.

364809187.title: Global CEO, MD & Director
364809187.pro_title: Member of the Board of Directors
364809187.biography: Mr. Mark Schuessler has been Global Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director of Yowie Group Ltd since January 05, 2018 and serves as its Director. Mr. Schuessler served as General Manager at Yowie North America Inc. since July 25, 2017. Mr. Schuessler served as the Global Chief Operating Officer of Yowie Group Ltd. since June 13, 2016 until January 2, 2018 and also served as its President. He is an experienced Senior Executive Leader with over 30 years' broad U.S. and international markets experience. He has extensive cross discipline and cross category operational and leadership experience in the consumer packaged goods industry with Doumak Inc., The Campbell Soup Company, Procter and Gamble and early financial roles in the printing and banking industries. He served as the President of Doumak Inc. since 2013 and also served as its Chief Operating Officer from 2008 to 2012 and again since 2013 and its Vice President of Sales and Marketing from 2008 to 2012 and again from 2002 to 2007 with significant sales and profit growth. He served as Sales Division Manager at The Campbell Soup Company from 2000 to 2002 and also served as its Sales Finance Manager from 1997 to 2000. He has a Finance Degree from Georgetown University and an MBA from the University of Chicago.

8384444.title: Company Secretary & Director
8384444.pro_title: Member of the Board of Directors
8384444.biography: Mr. Neville John Bassett, AM, B.Bus., FCA, has been Non-Executive Director at Blina Minerals NL since November 28, 2019. Mr. Bassett serves as Non-Executive Chairman and Company Secretary of Pointerra Limited and Quantify Technology Holdings Limited. Mr. Bassett has been a Company Secretary of Metalsearch Limited (formerly Laconia Resources Limited) since May 7, 2015, Australian Vanadium Limited since November 26, 2014 and Sinetech Limited (Exoma Energy Limited) since February 3, 2015. Mr. Bassett has been a Company Secretary of Yowie Group Ltd. since November 1, 2013 and serves as its Director from August 5, 2019. He has been Secretary of Surefire Resources NL since April 24, 2018. Mr. Bassett has been Treasurer and Councilor at the Royal Flying Doctor Service of Australia WA Section since 1991. He has experience and operating his own corporate consulting business, specialising in the area of corporate, financial and management advisory services. He served as Company Secretary of Zelda Therapeutics Limited until December 16, 2016. He served as Company Secretary at Gleneagle Gold Limited from May 2010. He served as Company Secretary of Kairiki Energy Limited from April 14, 2005 to June 14, 2016. He served as Company Secretary of ORH Limited. He served as a Company Secretary of WHL Energy Limited since February 5, 2016. He served as a Secretary of Australian Vanadium Limited (alternate name, Yellow Rock Resources Ltd.) since October 25, 2010. He served as a Secretary of Cycliq Group Limited (Modena Resources Ltd). He served as a Company Secretary of Connected IO Limited from July 13, 2001 to July 29, 2011 and Ardiden Limited (Alternative Name: Stratos Resources Limited) from December 14, 2007 to July 29, 2011. Mr. Bassett served as an Independent Consultant of BIR Financial Limited since March 12, 2007 and served as its Company Secretary from May 1, 2006 to March 12, 2007. He served as Company Secretary of Vector Resources Limited from February 2011 until January 4, 2018. He served as an Executive of Sun Biomedical Limited. He served as Company Secretary of MGM Wireless Limited from March 16, 1999 to December 21, 2009 and Soil Sub Technologies Ltd. from July 2016. He has consulted to a number of publicly listed companies and private company groups in a diversity of industry sectors such as stock broking, property and resources. He was involved with numerous public company listings and capital raisings. His involvement in the corporate arena has also taken in mergers and acquisitions and includes significant knowledge and exposure to the Australian financial markets. Mr. Bassett has a wealth of experience in matters pertaining to New World Cobalt Limited Act 2001, ASX listing requirements, corporate taxation and finance. He served as Company Secretary of Austsino Resources Group Limited from May 2009 to August 1, 2011 and served as its Secretary from March 16, 1999 to November 2006. He served as Company Secretary of Resource Mining Corporation Limited until May 2007. He was involved with a diverse range of Australian public listed companies in Directorial, company secretarial and financial roles. He served as Secretary of Arrow Minerals Limited (also known as Segue Resources Limited) from April 2, 2008 to July 13, 2011. He has been a Non-Executive Director of Pointerra Limited since February 4, 2016. He served as Non-Executive Chairman of Meteoric Resources NL since September 19, 2014 until December 4, 2017 and its Director since November 29, 2012 until December 4, 2017. Mr. Bassett served as the Non-Executive Chairman of New World Cobalt Limited (also known as Ram Resources Limited) from March 22, 2004 to October 31, 2017. He served as the Non-Executive Chairman and Director of Aleator Energy Limited from August 22, 2003 to October 12, 2004. He served as Non-Executive Director at Metalsearch Limited (formerly Laconia Resources Limited) since May 07, 2015 until October 16, 2019 and New World Cobalt Limited (also known as Ram Resources Limited) from March 22, 2004 to October 31, 2017. He has been Non-Executive Chairman of Auris Minerals Limited since April 2018 and has been its Director since April 20, 2018. He has been Director of RFDS Western Operations since 1997. He serves as Chairman at Westar Capital LLC. He serves as a Director of Contact Resources Ltd. He served as a Non-Executive Director at Vector Resources Limited from April 22, 2010 to January 4, 2018. He served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of Sinetech Limited from August 20, 2014 to May 13, 2016. He served as a Director of WHL Energy Limited from February 5, 2016 to March 1, 2017. He served as a Director of Quantify Technology Holdings Limited until March 1, 2017. He served as a Non-Executive Director at Cycliq Group Limited from September 14, 2006 to January 30, 2009, Mamba Minerals Limited from August 13, 2010 to August 13, 2013, Pinnacle VRB Ltd. from September 30, 2005 to October 12, 2006 and Cougar Energy Limited from September 30, 2005 to October 9, 2006. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Neurodiscovery Limited (Also Known As: Oncosil Medical Limited) from August 6, 2010 to March 14, 2012, Soil Sub Technologies Ltd. from July 2016, Champion Iron Limited until August 13, 2013, Moreton Resources Limited from September 30, 2005 to October 9, 2006 and Kairiki Energy Limited from September 28, 2010 to March 31, 2011. He has been a Non-Executive Director at PharmAust Limited since October 1, 2018. He is State Chairman and former National Director of a major not-for-profit organization. He is a Chartered Accountant specializing in corporate, financial and management advisory services. He has been involved with numerous public company listings and capital raisings. He has extensive experience in the Corporations Act, ASX listing requirements, corporate taxation and finance. Mr. Bassett holds a Bachelor of Business Degree from Curtin University of Technology.

594722202.title: Chief Financial Officer
594722202.biography: Mr. Wayne Brekke has been Chief Financial Officer of Yowie Group Limited since December 2018. A versatile, senior finance executive with over 30 years of broad US and international finance experience, Mr. Brekke have responsibility for the Yowie Group Finance, Accounting and IT functions. He is replacing current finance staff and reorganizing the function to Chicago. He is responsible for the Yowie Groupâ€™s financial reporting, strategic planning, budgeting, investor relations, cash management and information technology. Mr. Brekke has held extensive finance leadership positions in food, consumer products and manufacturing with companies such as, McDonaldâ€™s, Kraft Foods and AC Nielsen. Prior to joining Yowie, he was Group Controller for the Garvey Group, a subsidiary of Orora Ltd (ASX:ORA), from 2015, responsible for accounting, reporting and analysis for a multi-plant production operation. He successfully led the company-wide ERP implementation across multiple business units and was a key member of the companyâ€™s acquisition integration team focusing on efficiencies and consistent financial policies. Mr. Brekke has an MBA in Finance from DePaul University (Chicago, Illinois) and a Bachelor in Business Administration in Accountancy from the University of Notre Dame (South Bend, Indiana).

594726219.title: Global Chief Marketing Officer
594726219.biography: Ms. Cynthia Thayer has been Global Chief Marketing Officer of Yowie Group Limited since December 2018. Ms. Thayer is responsible for the Yowie groupâ€™s intellectual properties and brand equity. Ms. Thayer has over 25 years of marketing expertise in key areas including brand architecture development, market research, CPG consumer advertising across traditional and digital channels, retail and shopper marketing, licensing, toy design and new product development. She has responsibility for all marketing and new product development. She has broad marketing expertise in food, consumer products, manufacturing and advertising agencies with the Chamberlain Group, TPN, Flair Communications, Creata and the Marketing Store. She joined Yowie Group  from the largest global manufacturer of garage door openers, The Chamberlain Group, managing its newest product development growth area into the smart home category. She was a key player in bringing their newest smart technology brand to life from the ground up, then building out and implementing its go-to-market plan across TV advertising, digital advertising, SEO, social media, PR and retail merchandising. While at TPN and Creata, she successfully managed toy design, product development and licensing expertise from her work on McDonaldâ€™s Global Happy Meals, Nestle Brazil Easter eggs and Walmart baby/kids softlines. Her experience extends to identifying and collaborating with major movie and cartoon studios, as well as toy companies including Hasbro and Mattel. Ms. Thayer has a Bachelor of Arts in Communication from Hofstra University (New York).
